details.purpose: For the capture and reporting of details of the Sports Athlete Foot and Ankle Score (SAFAS). This is a patient reported outcomes measure (PROM).
details.use:
Use to record details of the Sports Athlete Foot and Ankle Score (SAFAS).
While openEHR archetypes are all freely available under an open license, the specific content of this archetype may be copyright protected. Any use of this archetype within implementations must be in compliance with the terms established by the copyright owners where a copyright exists.
details.misuse: Not to be used unless the terms of copyright have been observed (if a copyright exists).

Swollen foot or ankle
Patient-reported extent to which foot or ankle has been swollen during last week.
Questionnaire wording: To what extent has your foot/ankle been swollen during the last week?
Never
Foot or ankle has not been swollen in last week.
Rarely
Foot or ankle has rarely been swollen in last week.
Sometimes
Foot or ankle has sometimes been swollen in last week.
Often
Foot or ankle has often been swollen in last week.
Grinding or noise when moving foot or ankle
Patient-reported extent of feeling grinding, hearing clicking or any other type of noise when foot or ankle moved during last week.
Questionnaire wording: To what extent have you felt grinding, heard clicking or any other type of noise when your foot/ankle moved?
